              "content": "# scatter_chart\nScatter plots, bubble charts, and correlation with regression line\n\n# Scatter & Bubble Charts \u2014 Templates\n\nUse for: correlations, two-variable relationships, cross-sectional comparisons.\nAdd a regression line to show the overall trend.\n\n---\n\n## Template A \u2014 Scatter + Regression Line\n\nBest for: correlation between two numeric variables.\n\n```python\nimport altair as alt\n\ndf = _db.execute(\"\"\"\n    SELECT x_col, y_col, label\n    FROM your_table\n\"\"\").df()\n\nscatter = alt.Chart(df).mark_point(\n    filled=True,\n    color=PRIMARY,\n    size=SCATTER_SIZE,\n    opacity=SCATTER_OPACITY,\n).encode(\n    x=alt.X('x_col:Q', axis=alt.Axis(title='X Variable')),\n    y=alt.Y('y_col:Q', axis=alt.Axis(title='Y Variable')),\n    tooltip=[\n        alt.Tooltip('label:N', title='Label'),\n        alt.Tooltip('x_col:Q', title='X', format=',.2f'),\n        alt.Tooltip('y_col:Q', title='Y', format=',.2f'),\n    ]\n)\n\nregression = scatter.transform_regression(\n    'x_col', 'y_col'\n).mark_line(\n    color=ACCENT_AMBER, strokeWidth=1.5, strokeDash=[4, 3]\n)\n\nchart = gs_theme(scatter + regression, \"X vs Y Correlation\")\nsave_artifact(chart, \"X vs Y Correlation\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## Template B \u2014 Scatter Colored by Category\n\nBest for: showing how groups cluster or separate in two-dimensional space.\n\n```python\nimport altair as alt\n\ndf = _db.execute(\"\"\"\n    SELECT x_col, y_col, category, label\n    FROM your_table\n\"\"\").df()\n\nn_cats = df['category'].nunique()\n\nchart = alt.Chart(df).mark_point(\n    filled=True, size=SCATTER_SIZE, opacity=SCATTER_OPACITY\n).encode(\n    x=alt.X('x_col:Q', axis=alt.Axis(title='X Variable')),\n    y=alt.Y('y_col:Q', axis=alt.Axis(title='Y Variable')),\n    color=alt.Color('category:N',\n        scale=alt.Scale(range=CAT_PALETTE[:n_cats]),\n        legend=alt.Legend(title=None)),\n    tooltip=[\n        alt.Tooltip('label:N', title='Name'),\n        alt.Tooltip('category:N', title='Category'),\n        alt.Tooltip('x_col:Q', title='X', format=',.2f'),\n        alt.Tooltip('y_col:Q', title='Y', format=',.2f'),\n    ]\n)\n\nchart = gs_theme(chart, \"Category Scatter\")\nsave_artifact(chart, \"Category Scatter\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## Template C \u2014 Bubble Chart (size-encoded third dimension)\n\nBest for: showing a third variable via point size (e.g., GDP \u00d7 unemployment \u00d7 population).\n\n```python\nimport altair as alt\n\ndf = _db.execute(\"\"\"\n    SELECT x_col, y_col, size_col, label\n    FROM your_table\n\"\"\").df()\n\nchart = alt.Chart(df).mark_point(\n    filled=True, color=PRIMARY, opacity=SCATTER_OPACITY\n).encode(\n    x=alt.X('x_col:Q', axis=alt.Axis(title='X Variable')),\n    y=alt.Y('y_col:Q', axis=alt.Axis(title='Y Variable')),\n    size=alt.Size('size_col:Q',\n        scale=alt.Scale(range=[50, 1000]),\n        legend=alt.Legend(title='Size Metric')),\n    tooltip=[\n        alt.Tooltip('label:N', title='Name'),\n        alt.Tooltip('x_col:Q', title='X', format=',.2f'),\n        alt.Tooltip('y_col:Q', title='Y', format=',.2f'),\n        alt.Tooltip('size_col:Q', title='Size', format=',.0f'),\n    ]\n)\n\nchart = gs_theme(chart, \"Bubble Chart\")\nsave_artifact(chart, \"Bubble Chart\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## Rules\n\n- Always label axes clearly \u2014 field names alone are often not enough\n- Use `transform_regression` only when correlation is the point of the chart\n- For >500 points, reduce opacity to 0.4\u20130.5 to handle overplotting\n- Use `ACCENT_AMBER` for regression line \u2014 contrasts well against `PRIMARY` points\n- If points overlap heavily, consider a hexbin or histogram instead\n\n---\n**NEXT STEP:** Adapt the template above to the user's request. Call `run_python` with the complete script. Remember: `gs_theme`, `save_artifact`, `PRIMARY`, `CAT_PALETTE`, `_db`, and all constants are pre-imported \u2014 no imports needed. Use `:Q` for numbers, `:T` for dates, `:N` for categories. Do NOT call `.interactive()`.",
